🎫 Ticket Title

Delayed Image Scanning in RHACS After Operator Upgrade – Dev Cluster Showing Significant Scan Lag

⸻

📝 Ticket Description

Hi Team,

We are observing delayed image scanning behavior in our environment after performing a recent upgrade of Red Hat Advanced Cluster Security (RHACS).

Issue Details:
	•	The dev cluster contains a significantly higher number of deployments (~5370) compared to prod (~1603).
	•	Post-upgrade, many images in the dev cluster have not been scanned within the expected timeframe (typically a few hours), with several exceeding 12–24 hours.
	•	In contrast, the prod cluster (not recently upgraded) shows normal scan activity with up-to-date scan times.

Environment Details:
	•	Total secured clusters: ~7
	•	Dev cluster has multiple stages (e.g., unit test, dev), contributing to higher image volume.
	•	Scanner components (scanner-v4-indexer, scanner-db, central) are running and healthy.
	•	Logs indicate scanning activity is ongoing, but scan throughput appears slower than expected.

Observations:
	•	Sorting images by scan time shows a large portion of images in dev exceeding 12 hours since last scan.
	•	No explicit scan queue or backlog metrics visible in UI.
	•	This behavior started after the operator upgrade.

Questions / Clarification Needed:
	1.	Is it expected behavior for RHACS to take 24–48 hours to re-scan images across all secured clusters after an upgrade?
	2.	Does RHACS re-index or re-scan all images post-upgrade, potentially causing backlog?
	3.	Are there recommended configurations (e.g., scaling scanner components) to improve scan throughput in high-volume environments?
	4.	Is there a way to monitor scan backlog or queue more explicitly?

Request:
Kindly confirm whether this behavior is expected and advise if any tuning or configuration changes are required to improve scan performance.

